    {
      "id": "75ff2eb7_4992548f",
      "file_path": "feature-server-pool/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/serverpool/TargetLock.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": null,
      "message": "I think we're going to have to discuss this.  One of the performance boosts that logger provides is that it doesn't bother invoking toString() unless it determines that the given logging level is enabled.\n\nIn addition, I think this will create a whole new set of sonar complaints that you shouldn't do anything \"complex\" when invoking logger without putting an \"if(logger.isInfoEnbled())\" around it.\n\nPretty sure that none of the UUIDs have to be cleaned before logging, nor do integers, so just keys and owner keys, but I'm guessing they don't need to be cleaned either unless DCAE is giving us garbage - if so, we should probably clean the events on input to drools-pdp rather than in every logging statement.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-01 23:34:17.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
